title.rendered: Delhi vs Gujarat, India Women’s League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Delhi: Meg Lanning (c), Shafali Verma, Alice Capsey, Jemimah Rodrigues, Marizanne Kapp, Jess Jonassen, Taniya Bhatia (wk), Arundhati Reddy, Radha Yadav, Shikha Pandey, Tara Norris

Gujarat: Sophia Dunkley, Sabbhineni Meghana, Harleen Deol, Annabel Sutherland, Ashleigh Gardner, Dayalan Hemalatha, Sneh Rana (c), Sushma Verma (wk), Kim Garth, Tanuja Kanwar, Mansi Joshi

Pitch Report

Venue: Brabourne Stadium, Mumbai

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 162

2nd innings average score: 169

Wickets per innings: 5

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

Lahore vs Peshawar Pakistan T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Bangladesh vs Ireland, 1st ODI 2023: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Brabourne has brought the best out of Ashleigh Gardner in the tournament: six of her seven wickets (at a strike rate of eight) and 27 of 52 runs have come at the venue.

Marizanne Kapp picked up a fifer when the sides clashed last week. Her recent form has been splendid too: 14 wickets and 136 runs (at 27) in the last 10 matches.

Shafali Verma has aggregated 169 runs at 42 at the venue, including two fifties.

Meg Lanning has registered two fifties and a thirty to aggregate 221 runs at 55 in the tournament.

Tara Norris grabbed a fifer when she last bowled at the venue.

Since getting out for a duck in the tournament opener, Harleen Deol has scored 155 runs at 39.

Alice Capsey and Kim Garth have featured in the Best11 in four of the last five matches.

Jemimah Rodrigues has scored 158 runs in the last five innings at an average of 53 and a strike rate of 147.

Sabbhineni Meghana averages just 13 in the last nine matches, with a top score of 26.

Six fifties and six thirties have been scored by the top four batters in the last three games at the venue, while spinners have scalped 74% of the wickets.
